WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:07.638 --> 00:00:10.774
[theme music playing]

2
00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:18.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

3
00:00:27.116 --> 00:00:29.209
["Doing It To Death" playing]

4
00:00:30.502 --> 00:00:33.305
[Hannah] <i>You've heard of
the butterfly effect. right?</i>

5
00:00:35.007 --> 00:00:37.800
<i>That if a butterfly flaps its
wings at just the right time</i>

6
00:00:37.801 --> 00:00:39.436
<i>in just the right place...</i>

7
00:00:41.763 --> 00:00:44.858
<i>it can cause a hurricane
thousands of miles away.</i>

8
00:00:50.439 --> 00:00:51.656
[woman] Hold on.

9
00:00:58.405 --> 00:00:59.822
Is Justin here?

10
00:00:59.823 --> 00:01:02.408
Haven't seen him for days.
I thought he was with you.

11
00:01:02.409 --> 00:01:04.461
He told me he was going home last night.

12
00:01:04.745 --> 00:01:06.120
Yeah. well. he didn't.

13
00:01:06.121 --> 00:01:08.590
- [man] Who is it. Am?
- Justin's girlfriend.

14
00:01:09.791 --> 00:01:11.343
[sighs]

15
00:01:11.752 --> 00:01:13.011
Girlfriend. huh?

16
00:01:13.587 --> 00:01:16.848
Tell that little shit that his
mother is worried sick. all right?

17
00:01:17.382 --> 00:01:20.143
Yeah. She looks it.

18
00:01:21.178 --> 00:01:23.471
Tell him call her today or
don't bother coming home.

19
00:01:23.472 --> 00:01:26.474
<i>♪ Heads up We're in a dead club... ♪</i>

20
00:01:26.475 --> 00:01:28.193
[Hannah]<i> It's chaos theory.</i>

21
00:01:28.685 --> 00:01:32.697
<i>But. see. chaos theory
isn't exactly about chaos.</i>

22
00:01:33.273 --> 00:01:37.527
<i>It's about how a tiny change in a
big system can affect everything.</i>

23
00:01:37.528 --> 00:01:39.028
<i>♪ Doing it to death ♪</i>

24
00:01:39.029 --> 00:01:40.988
- Fuck! What the fuck?
- [laughs]

25
00:01:40.989 --> 00:01:42.990
Dude. it's time to wakey.

26
00:01:42.991 --> 00:01:45.409
I'm rolling in ten. if
you feel like school.

27
00:01:45.410 --> 00:01:47.128
Oh. shit!

28
00:01:47.329 --> 00:01:50.081
- What's with the fucking water?
- Just having some fun.

29
00:01:50.082 --> 00:01:51.883
[mocking] "I'm just having some fun."

30
00:01:52.584 --> 00:01:55.753
Justy. you know you're welcome
here all the damn time. buddy.

31
00:01:55.754 --> 00:01:57.713
but I thought you were
going home last night.

32
00:01:57.714 --> 00:01:59.590
Yeah. that guy Seth is back.

33
00:01:59.591 --> 00:02:01.926
- Meth Seth?
- Yeth.

34
00:02:01.927 --> 00:02:03.353
[both laugh]

35
00:02:04.054 --> 00:02:07.274
And that's all. right? Just Meth Seth?

36
00:02:07.558 --> 00:02:09.401
Yeah. just that asshole.

37
00:02:09.560 --> 00:02:11.602
I can't deal with him. you know that.

38
00:02:11.603 --> 00:02:14.197
'Cause your girlfriend's texting me now.

39
00:02:16.733 --> 00:02:19.902
Brother. you know that Seth or whatever.

40
00:02:19.903 --> 00:02:22.581
I got your back. always.

41
00:02:22.906 --> 00:02:24.116
Yeah. I know.

42
00:02:24.141 --> 00:02:27.034
Whatever you did. if you
even fucking did anything.

43
00:02:27.035 --> 00:02:28.545
we can take care of it.

44
00:02:29.705 --> 00:02:31.205
I mean anything.

45
00:02:31.206 --> 00:02:32.549
You know my one rule.

46
00:02:33.150 --> 00:02:34.250
Keep you clean.

47
00:02:34.251 --> 00:02:36.595
Keep me clean. All right.

48
00:02:37.129 --> 00:02:39.890
And Jessica. take
care of her. all right?

49
00:02:40.215 --> 00:02:41.516
She's your girl.

50
00:02:43.468 --> 00:02:44.594
You want some breakfast?

51
00:02:44.595 --> 00:02:47.722
Marisa the maid's here
making some Mexican shit.

52
00:02:47.723 --> 00:02:50.483
[chuckles] You know
she's Guatemalan. right?

53
00:02:51.018 --> 00:02:52.152
Sure.

54
00:02:52.603 --> 00:02:54.362
- Hungry?
- Yeah.

55
00:02:55.564 --> 00:02:59.159
[Hannah] <i>Chaos theory.</i>
<i>Sounds dramatic. but it's not.</i>

56
00:03:00.569 --> 00:03:02.037
<i>Ask a mathematician.</i>

57
00:03:02.446 --> 00:03:05.540
<i>Or better yet. ask someone
who's been in a hurricane.</i>

58
00:03:05.949 --> 00:03:08.367
<i>♪ We're double sixing it ♪</i>

59
00:03:08.368 --> 00:03:13.080
<i>♪ Night after night after night ♪</i>

60
00:03:13.081 --> 00:03:15.791
<i>♪ We're double sixing it ♪</i>

61
00:03:15.792 --> 00:03:20.180
<i>♪ Night after night after night ♪</i>

62
00:03:23.133 --> 00:03:24.267
Wanna help?

63
00:03:25.552 --> 00:03:27.011
Do I want help?

64
00:03:27.012 --> 00:03:30.398
Do you want to help? Put up posters.

65
00:03:33.185 --> 00:03:34.685
No. no thanks. Marcus.

66
00:03:34.686 --> 00:03:36.321
Come on. school spirit.

67
00:03:36.605 --> 00:03:38.773
All right? Making a contribution.

68
00:03:38.774 --> 00:03:39.991
Giving back.

69
00:03:40.400 --> 00:03:42.193
Giving back to who. exactly?

70
00:03:42.194 --> 00:03:44.496
[band warming up]

71
00:03:44.905 --> 00:03:46.781
Why are they playing in the courtyard?

72
00:03:46.782 --> 00:03:49.709
Uh. yeah. They asked student
council. Thought it was a great idea.

73
00:03:50.160 --> 00:03:51.628
Got a concert tonight.

74
00:03:52.704 --> 00:03:54.798
We got some glum chums.

75
00:03:55.791 --> 00:03:58.292
[Hannah] <i>Alex Standall.</i>
<i>You caused the hurricane.</i>

76
00:03:58.293 --> 00:03:59.427
<i>It's your turn.</i>

77
00:03:59.711 --> 00:04:01.128
F.M.L. forever.

78
00:04:01.129 --> 00:04:02.672
F.M.L. forever.

79
00:04:02.673 --> 00:04:04.173
F.M.L. forever.

80
00:04:04.174 --> 00:04:07.185
[Hannah] <i>Little did I know</i>
<i>you would F. my L. forever.</i>

81
00:04:08.512 --> 00:04:10.930
<i>Little did I know you
would be my hurricane.</i>

82
00:04:10.931 --> 00:04:12.348
- Hey. Alex.
- Hey.

83
00:04:12.349 --> 00:04:14.642
- You okay?
- Yeah. I just... I overslept.

84
00:04:14.643 --> 00:04:17.019
Mr. McLean wants us to
start with "Take Five."

85
00:04:17.020 --> 00:04:20.031
- He thinks that'll raise spirits.
- Love me some Brubeck.

86
00:04:20.315 --> 00:04:24.235
Though of course it was written
by Paul Desmond. but whatever.

87
00:04:24.236 --> 00:04:27.330
If they want a spirit-raiser.
how about "Gloomy Sunday"?

88
00:04:27.864 --> 00:04:31.084
Are you serious? That
song's totally depressing.

89
00:04:31.451 --> 00:04:33.703
Or it's beautiful. if you have taste.

90
00:04:33.704 --> 00:04:35.463
Or if you're suicidal.

91
00:04:41.670 --> 00:04:42.670
Way to go. Troy.

92
00:04:42.671 --> 00:04:44.296
Aw. shit.

93
00:04:44.297 --> 00:04:46.632
Was he friends with Hannah
Baker? I didn't know.

94
00:04:46.633 --> 00:04:48.935
[Hannah] <i>Maybe you
think I'm being silly.</i>

95
00:04:49.678 --> 00:04:53.013
<i>I'm some stupid girl who gets all
worked up over a little thing.</i>

96
00:04:53.014 --> 00:04:54.941
<i>But little things matter.</i>

97
00:04:56.852 --> 00:05:00.739
<i>For instance. you never told me
when you started dating Jessica.</i>

98
00:05:02.774 --> 00:05:05.160
<i>But I remember just how it ended.</i>

99
00:05:05.777 --> 00:05:07.579
<i>- With your list.</i>
- [sighs]

100
00:05:10.115 --> 00:05:12.125
Is "Gloomy Sunday" really a song?

101
00:05:13.076 --> 00:05:16.171
Yeah. Google "Hungarian Suicide Song."

102
00:05:16.872 --> 00:05:18.465
I'll take your word for it.

103
00:05:21.334 --> 00:05:22.469
Alex.

104
00:05:24.254 --> 00:05:25.555
Can we. um...

105
00:05:27.549 --> 00:05:28.767
talk about this?

106
00:05:31.678 --> 00:05:33.387
What is there to talk about?

107
00:05:33.388 --> 00:05:35.940
- Is Hannah telling the truth?
- What do you think?

108
00:05:36.224 --> 00:05:38.058
Did you do what she said you did?

109
00:05:38.059 --> 00:05:39.194
Did you?

110
00:05:40.520 --> 00:05:44.240
Alex. "Take the 'A'
Train." with your solo.

111
00:05:44.774 --> 00:05:46.066
All right. well.

112
00:05:46.067 --> 00:05:49.412
I guess if I'm gonna be happy.
may as well do it with the Duke.

113
00:05:50.655 --> 00:05:52.948
- [drumsticks tapping]
- [band playing mellow rock]

114
00:05:52.949 --> 00:05:56.086
[Hannah] <i>Alex. we hadn't talked</i>
<i>since you two got together.</i>

115
00:05:57.382 --> 00:06:02.604
<i>And then it seemed like maybe you
might not be together anymore.</i>

116
00:06:07.339 --> 00:06:09.390
- Hey. Jess.
- Hey.

117
00:06:09.591 --> 00:06:10.809
Mrs. Antilly?

118
00:06:11.176 --> 00:06:12.310
Yeah.

119
00:06:13.011 --> 00:06:14.229
Everything okay?

120
00:06:14.721 --> 00:06:16.013
What. like in the world?

121
00:06:16.014 --> 00:06:17.732
Or with you.

122
00:06:18.183 --> 00:06:19.400
Yeah.

123
00:06:19.601 --> 00:06:23.020
You could drop by our office later.
if you want to make a full report.

124
00:06:23.021 --> 00:06:24.396
Our office?

125
00:06:24.397 --> 00:06:25.648
Monet's.

126
00:06:25.649 --> 00:06:27.909
Oh. Yeah. right.

127
00:06:28.026 --> 00:06:29.619
I forgot about that.

128
00:06:29.945 --> 00:06:31.195
The office thing.

129
00:06:31.196 --> 00:06:32.905
Yeah. It's been a while.

130
00:06:32.906 --> 00:06:35.333
Yeah. there's just so much going on.

131
00:06:38.651 --> 00:06:39.953
Male!

132
00:06:39.978 --> 00:06:41.779
Females.

133
00:06:42.249 --> 00:06:45.593
Hey. how about a Monet's reunion today?

134
00:06:46.378 --> 00:06:50.390
You have a few drink selections
left on your great menu journey.

135
00:06:50.423 --> 00:06:51.891
You were so committed once.

136
00:06:52.425 --> 00:06:54.385
Yeah. commitment's hard for Alex.

137
00:06:54.386 --> 00:06:57.012
At least I have the ability
to try something new in life.

138
00:06:57.013 --> 00:06:59.148
[Hannah] <i>Is that why you did it. Alex?</i>

139
00:07:01.059 --> 00:07:02.235
Mrs. Baker.

140
00:07:03.186 --> 00:07:05.113
Hi. I wasn't expecting you.

141
00:07:05.689 --> 00:07:07.398
Olivia. Please.

142
00:07:07.399 --> 00:07:09.284
Yeah. Well. come on in.

143
00:07:10.610 --> 00:07:13.404
Thank you for making the time.

144
00:07:13.405 --> 00:07:15.039
I-I. uh...

145
00:07:15.448 --> 00:07:16.740
I know how busy you are.

146
00:07:16.741 --> 00:07:18.117
No. not at all.

147
00:07:18.118 --> 00:07:20.128
- [shuts door]
- What can I do for you?

148
00:07:23.623 --> 00:07:25.291
Well. I was. um.

149
00:07:25.292 --> 00:07:30.096
I'm wondering if you could tell me
something about Hannah's school life.

150
00:07:30.839 --> 00:07:33.215
I mean. was she unhappy here?

151
00:07:33.216 --> 00:07:34.350
Well...

152
00:07:34.634 --> 00:07:37.011
I don't think I can answer that.

153
00:07:37.012 --> 00:07:39.555
I know you can't possibly
know every student.

154
00:07:39.556 --> 00:07:44.110
but my husband and I. we're
still trying to understand.

155
00:07:46.605 --> 00:07:49.199
At home. Hannah was... Well. I mean...

156
00:07:49.649 --> 00:07:52.234
sometimes she would run around the house

157
00:07:52.235 --> 00:07:55.279
singing show tunes in funny
voices and showering us with hugs.

158
00:07:55.280 --> 00:07:57.290
and other times...

159
00:07:58.074 --> 00:08:02.939
she was quiet and moody and it'd
be hard to get a word out of her.

160
00:08:02.964 --> 00:08:06.559
- Sure.
- But nothing she did told us she was...

161
00:08:08.001 --> 00:08:09.218
capable of...

162
00:08:09.243 --> 00:08:12.759
I'm afraid I'm going to have to
stop you right there. Mrs. Baker.

163
00:08:12.784 --> 00:08:14.924
I'm terribly sorry for your loss.

164
00:08:14.925 --> 00:08:18.761
and I wish I could
offer you what you need.

165
00:08:18.762 --> 00:08:20.813
but I just can't.

166
00:08:22.557 --> 00:08:24.901
Now that lawyers are involved.

167
00:08:25.936 --> 00:08:27.186
What are you saying?

168
00:08:27.187 --> 00:08:29.855
What I'm saying is that.
in light of your lawsuit.

169
00:08:29.856 --> 00:08:33.451
I shouldn't even be talking to you.

170
00:08:33.860 --> 00:08:35.078
I see.

171
00:08:36.404 --> 00:08:37.696
So then why are you?

172
00:08:37.697 --> 00:08:40.616
You and your husband are
members of our school community.

173
00:08:40.617 --> 00:08:44.337
and we want nothing more than
to support you during this time.

174
00:08:47.248 --> 00:08:50.093
I can only imagine your grief.

175
00:08:50.877 --> 00:08:54.472
You can't imagine the first
thing about my life right now.

176
00:08:56.299 --> 00:08:58.008
- [sobbing]
- [door opens]

177
00:08:58.009 --> 00:09:00.678
- [girl 1] Bryce is a total vampire.
- [girl 2 chuckles]

178
00:09:00.679 --> 00:09:02.429
That thing on your neck is huge.

179
00:09:02.430 --> 00:09:04.107
Oh. I know. right?

180
00:09:07.102 --> 00:09:08.403
[exhales sharply]

181
00:09:12.649 --> 00:09:13.992
[gasping breath]

182
00:09:15.568 --> 00:09:17.412
[whimpers]

183
00:09:28.540 --> 00:09:31.092
[Hannah] <i>Maybe you say
it's nothing. Alex.</i>

184
00:09:32.711 --> 00:09:34.012
<i>It's just words.</i>

185
00:09:48.226 --> 00:09:49.351
[sniffles]

186
00:09:49.352 --> 00:09:50.737
[camera shutter clicks]

187
00:09:55.442 --> 00:09:56.826
[camera shutter clicks]

188
00:09:57.610 --> 00:09:58.694
Seriously. Tyler?

189
00:09:58.695 --> 00:10:02.665
If you're going to do a memorial.
I'm going to take pictures.

190
00:10:03.783 --> 00:10:06.169
Mrs. Baker. Hi.

191
00:10:07.829 --> 00:10:09.547
I'm Courtney Crimsen.

192
00:10:13.251 --> 00:10:15.261
I'm so sorry for your loss.

193
00:10:15.795 --> 00:10:17.138
I hope you like it.

194
00:10:17.672 --> 00:10:19.057
People keep adding to it.

195
00:10:19.382 --> 00:10:22.685
Um. every day there's
another card or more flowers.

196
00:10:23.386 --> 00:10:27.014
All these people were Hannah's friends?

197
00:10:27.015 --> 00:10:30.443
Mm-hmm. She had so many friends and...

198
00:10:31.394 --> 00:10:33.571
we all miss her so much.

199
00:10:34.022 --> 00:10:37.408
Anyone who knew Hannah would
know that she hated roses.

200
00:10:40.236 --> 00:10:42.205
She thought they were a cliché.

201
00:10:42.572 --> 00:10:44.957
[bell rings]

202
00:10:53.875 --> 00:10:55.968
["Whatever You Want" playing]

203
00:10:56.836 --> 00:10:58.221
[Clay] Hannah.

204
00:10:59.005 --> 00:11:00.306
Hey. Hannah.

205
00:11:01.508 --> 00:11:02.892
- Hey.
- Morning. Helmet.

206
00:11:04.094 --> 00:11:05.353
Urgent question.

207
00:11:05.595 --> 00:11:08.481
Have you noticed anything
weird about Alex lately?

208
00:11:09.099 --> 00:11:13.018
Um... Well. his hair's
weird. but that's not new.

209
00:11:13.019 --> 00:11:14.895
His hair is awesome.

210
00:11:14.896 --> 00:11:18.398
I didn't say it wasn't awesome.
it's just. like. distinctive.

211
00:11:18.399 --> 00:11:20.025
And he's an amazing dresser.

212
00:11:20.026 --> 00:11:21.985
I mean. you could take a few lessons.

213
00:11:21.986 --> 00:11:23.070
I totally could.

214
00:11:23.071 --> 00:11:25.447
And I'm glad we got
around to my failings

215
00:11:25.448 --> 00:11:27.792
because I was wondering
when we would get to that.

216
00:11:28.660 --> 00:11:30.253
Are you working tonight?

217
00:11:30.411 --> 00:11:31.995
Yeah. we're both on at six.

218
00:11:31.996 --> 00:11:34.215
I mean. I think. On the schedule.

219
00:11:35.625 --> 00:11:38.377
So. speaking of tonight. I
don't know if you know this.

220
00:11:38.378 --> 00:11:41.347
but there's a penumbral
lunar eclipse at 11:49.

221
00:11:41.881 --> 00:11:43.015
A what?

222
00:11:44.050 --> 00:11:45.884
The Earth's shadow is the penumbra.

223
00:11:45.885 --> 00:11:47.886
Tonight. the moon is
gonna pass through it.

224
00:11:47.887 --> 00:11:51.056
Last show is at nine. and if we
clean fast. and we probably can.

225
00:11:51.057 --> 00:11:54.560
because no kids are coming to that
English movie because it's boring.

226
00:11:54.561 --> 00:11:59.866
we could get out in time. and I
could maybe point it out to you.

227
00:12:00.316 --> 00:12:01.450
If you want.

228
00:12:02.986 --> 00:12:04.704
You want to show me the moon?

229
00:12:05.738 --> 00:12:08.282
There would be a shadow.
Not like a full eclipse.

230
00:12:08.283 --> 00:12:10.418
You wouldn't exactly see the...

231
00:12:10.702 --> 00:12:11.836
But. yeah.

232
00:12:12.245 --> 00:12:13.495
[chuckles]

233
00:12:13.496 --> 00:12:16.757
You should. like. patent yourself.

234
00:12:18.334 --> 00:12:21.137
And. yes. I will look
at the moon with you.

235
00:12:21.921 --> 00:12:23.514
I might even howl.

236
00:12:23.923 --> 00:12:25.641
Cool. Cool.

237
00:12:26.050 --> 00:12:28.144
So. yeah. I'll see you tonight.

238
00:12:31.180 --> 00:12:32.398
[locker doom slams]

239
00:12:40.732 --> 00:12:42.867
Anyways. is Justin still missing?

240
00:12:43.526 --> 00:12:46.537
He's not missing. I
know exactly where he is.

241
00:12:49.991 --> 00:12:51.783
[sighs] So he's at Bryce's.

242
00:12:51.784 --> 00:12:52.910
Maybe you should go.

243
00:12:52.911 --> 00:12:54.995
I shouldn't have to
go. He should be here.

244
00:12:54.996 --> 00:12:58.248
Then go get him. Drag him back
to school by his perfect hair.

245
00:12:58.249 --> 00:12:59.750
Right.

246
00:12:59.751 --> 00:13:00.918
You know what?

247
00:13:00.919 --> 00:13:04.046
Tell him that you entered
him into that costume contest.

248
00:13:04.047 --> 00:13:05.547
Two hundred bucks.

249
00:13:05.548 --> 00:13:08.351
Yeah. maybe he could dress
up as my actual boyfriend.

250
00:13:09.218 --> 00:13:12.387
[Mr. Porter] <i>I spoke to Justin. but
now I need to speak to Alex Standall.</i>

251
00:13:12.388 --> 00:13:16.433
He dated Jessica Davis.
who I spoke to yesterday.

